helptext.en:
Address Parts

To better represent the complexity of addresses each constituent part has been modeled.

Building Name

Use to record the actual name of a Heritage Asset where known.

Street

Use to record the name of the street where the Heritage Asset is located.

Town or City

Use to record the name of the town or city where the Heritage Asset is located.

County

Use to record the name of the county where the Heritage Asset is located.

Postcode

Use to record the postal code assigned to the Heritage Asset's location.

Townland

Use to record the name of the townland where the Heritage Asset is located.

Council

Use to record the name of the council responsible for the Heritage Asset.

Area Name

Use to record the name of the area where the Heritage Asset is located.

Area Type

Use to specify the type of area (e.g., district, barony) where the Heritage Asset is located.

Irish Grid Reference

Use to record the grid reference coordinates for the Heritage Asset's location using various formats, Alphanumeric TM65, Absolute TM65 or Long/Lat.

Location Description

Use to provide a detailed description of the Heritage Asset's location. This can include landmarks, nearby intersections, or other notable features.
